The implication of this approach is that computers are deterministic: if ci=
rcuit X is open, then the proposition represented by X is true; 1 plus 1 is=
 always 2; clicking =E2=80=9Cback=E2=80=9D on your browser will exit this p=
age. There are, of course, a huge number of abstractions and massive amount=
s of logic between an individual transistor and any action we might take wi=
th a computer =E2=80=94 and an effectively infinite number of places for bu=
gs =E2=80=94 but the appropriate mental model for a computer is that they d=
o exactly what they are told (indeed, a bug is not the computer making a mi=
stake, but rather a manifestation of the programmer telling the computer to=
 do the wrong thing)=E2=80=A6

Large language models, though, with their probabilistic approach, are in ma=
ny domains shockingly intuitive, and yet can hallucinate and are downright =
terrible at math; that is why the most compelling plug-in OpenAI launched w=
as from Wolfram|Alpha. Stephen Wolfram explained ( https://writings.stephen=
wolfram.com/2023/01/wolframalpha-as-the-way-to-bring-computational-knowledg=
e-superpowers-to-chatgpt/ ) :

For decades there=E2=80=99s been a dichotomy in thinking about AI between =
=E2=80=9Cstatistical approaches=E2=80=9D of the kind ChatGPT uses, and =E2=
=80=9Csymbolic approaches=E2=80=9D that are in effect the starting point fo=
r Wolfram|Alpha. But now=E2=80=94thanks to the success of ChatGPT=E2=80=94a=
s well as all the work we=E2=80=99ve done in making Wolfram|Alpha understan=
d natural language=E2=80=94there=E2=80=99s finally the opportunity to combi=
ne these to make something much stronger than either could ever achieve on =
their own.

That is the exact combination that happened, which led to the title of that=
 Article:

The fact this works so well is itself a testament to what Assistant AI=E2=
=80=99s are, and are not: they are not computing as we have previously unde=
rstood it; they are shockingly human in their way of =E2=80=9Cthinking=E2=
=80=9D and communicating. And frankly, I would have had a hard time solving=
 those three questions as well =E2=80=94 that=E2=80=99s what computers are =
for! And now ChatGPT has a computer of its own.

I still think the concept was incredibly elegant, but there was just one pr=
oblem: the user interface was terrible. You had to get a plugin from the =
=E2=80=9Cmarketplace=E2=80=9D, then pre-select it before you began a conver=
sation, and only then would you get workable results after a too-long proce=
ss where ChatGPT negotiated with the plugin provider in question on the ans=
wer.

This new model somewhat alleviates the problem: now, instead of having to s=
elect the correct plug-in (and thus restart your chat), you simply go direc=
tly to the GPT in question. In other words, if I want to create a poster, I=
 don=E2=80=99t enable the Canva plugin in ChatGPT, I go to Canva GPT in the=
